<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-11-03T19:48:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-11-03T19:48:00-05:00" n="801" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d801">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.51/408: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Spencer</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-11-03T19:00:00-05:48"><hi rend="italic">November 3,
                                        1920—7 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 11:45
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>77. Semiofficial newspaper published yesterday afternoon <hi rend="italic">acuerdo</hi> dated October 23 fixing War Department
                            expenditures for November at 166,000 pesos representing probable economy
                            of over 200,000 compared with recent months. Government adopted these
                            projects with only minor alterations and considers complete adoption of
                            reformed budget with important economies in other departments during
                            this week.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Spencer</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>